caption: Very tasty Moroccan food. Cash only.

I visited Morocco in 2015 and I could never find anything that really felt authentic until I ordered from here. The food is SO good and tastes just like the amazing food I tried in Morocco.  If you have never tried a Chicken Bastilla (sometimes referred to as Pastilla) you need to! It's so unique. Fair warning - it is a sweet and savory dish with almonds and chicken and their version brought back all of the memories when I ate it.  Their lamb is incredible and so is the soup, but everything I've had so far has been really great! We've mostly ordered through DoorDash, so we were a bit surprised when we picked up takeout and learned they were cash only.  Cannot recommend enough!

The food here is amazing! The waiter said "Its Moroccan, so it must be special", and boy was he right. It was also nice that he was very helpful and actually had a backstory for certain things on the menu.

We come here today (me and my wife )to this Excellent authentic Moroccan food and kind friendly service (thank you  Imad ). We have very much enjoyed the Mixt grill . The soup Harira . taktouka,bakoula and shrimps  appetizers - all very flavorful and tasty!  - out if this world! We highly recommend Chokran  restaurant as one of the best Moroccan restaurants in Chicago area.👍
My favorite Marocain place, best food and service!
Great food and staff
Love love love this place. The best Moroccan food in the country.
LOVE this place. Ordered out tonight for the first time in ages. It is so fresh, and always consistent. I highly recommend! The Hummus, Beet Salad and Moroccan Chicken are amazing!
The food was amazing! Can’t wait to come again.
Amazing chicken bastilla. I ate it so fast I didn’t have time for a picture 😂

I would have rated a 4, but the portion size I received of my zaalouk was ridiculously small. It did taste smokey, which was decent at best. I had to add lemon for flavor. I also ordered chicken couscous. I’ve had plenty of homemade couscous in my day by Moroccans and I just wasn’t impressed. Please add more flavor to dishes. I ordered via Uber Eats.
Couscous so delicious, clean restaurant,

This place is truly a diamond in the rough.  Simply a perfection combination of flavors that will rock your kasbah.  The chicken Bastilla had this great balance of sweet and savory with the shredded chicken, couscous, and almonds.  And the lamb fez cooked in the tagine was fall-off-the-bone tender. When you combine it with the prunes and almonds its magic that will make you weak in the knees.
Food was absolutely amazing..Aimad was our waiter and gave us great recommendations and super friendly.Highly recommend the Chicken Morrocon Tagien.Great fresh food made from scratch.

Authentic Moroccan food with great service! This place is not just a great restaurant but we learned that Shokran but a hub for Moroccan culture. Our server shared some amazing insight about the Arabic Language as we ate an amazing meal of chicken coucous and tagine.  I’ve been looking for a real Moroccan place for so long and we finally found it! Will definitely come again.

I had the Lamb Casablanca and the Beef meatballs here. The flavor was okay with a decent-small portion for both dishes. However, it was a little expensive for the food we got so it does not encourage me to come back.  Overall: decent Moroccan food with a high price tag.
Expensive and the food was not authentic
I had a long layover at O'Hare and this was a great place to stop off for dinner!

This place blew my mind in what I thought Moroccan cuisine could taste like. The lamb was fall of the bone tender and flavorful. Portions are giant. Whatever sauce they use to bath the couscous was divine. I will be visiting this place again for certain.

First time there all it was delicious the Salad and Casablanca Tagine with a cup of min tea, the service makes you feel welcome and a quality prices I will came back again, I'm so in love with Moroccan Food. Baraka Allah fika to this restaurant..
Great place and food.

It's decent, but a bit pricey. It's good for a date, special occasion or take out if you're a thrifty buyer! I got some beef and chicken skewers pretty good. My first Moroccan but this is not my last! :-O

Tasty Moroccan food prepared with care and attention. I am obsessed with the mint tea, and the Chicken Bastille. The portions of the couscous plates are exceedingly generous. The lentil soup is fantastic as well.
Yummy maraccon food

This, is a tasty restaurant! I was blown away with how well our food was prepared. BYOB and affordable dining.  I'd recommend getting a few apps and sharing a couple meals around the table. You'll want to try everything.

(Translated by Google) Not bad Everything is fine but please change the chicken! The rest is so good but the chicken not really not  (Original) Pas mal Tout est très bien mais s'il vous plaît, changez le poulet ! Le reste est tellement bon mais le poulet non vraiment pas

This is a great place to get Moroccan food, though it is a bit off the path from the center of Chicago. However, if you are in the area, it is a good option for getting some great food. The prices can be a bit high, and the establishment itself is a bit small, but it is worth coming if you are in the area and have a hankering for some Moroccan food
Awesome Moroccan food.
This place as advertised isna real hidden gem. The food and service here are phenomenal and it has a real family style dinning dining experience.  I definitely will return.

This place is a treasure. We come here every year for a family reunion, and we always look forward to it. Moroccan food is a mix of Arab/Mediterranean/African/French. Staff are very friendly and knowledgable and passionate about the food.

Excellent food, charming staff and very reasonable prices - will definitely go back!  You probably wouldn't expect to find such a warm, inviting restaurant so close to the expressway, but Shokran is a hidden gem!  My friend and I shared the hummus (delicious with warm pita), and then she had the Lamb Atlas tagine (tender, flavorful and soothing like a delicious stew) and I had the Chicken Bastilla (generally served as a shared app, but I ordered it as my entree because I was curious - and I was rewarded with a delightfully sweet and filling meal).  BYOB so great for the budget as well.  Can't wait to return!
Incredible food, great service, and a welcome cultural lesson.
Great food in intimate, cozy settings. BYOB. my favorite lamb in the World. Highly recommended.
It is good
It was a really good restaurant the food was awesome and the staff was really great and friendly I am from North Africa and I know the Moroccan food And their food ready taste like a traditional dish
If you are up to good comfort food, this is your place.

I wanted to live this place, but I didn’t. My husband is Moroccan and we both agreed, the food was good, but not great. We ordered a few things to try them out.  *Veggie Sampler - Good, but needed some seasoning. *Bread - Not Moroccan *Harira - Authentic and best thing we had. *Bastilla - Chicken was extremely dry with made it all hard to eat because the cinnamon and sugar only dry it out more. *Chicken Casablanca Tagine - the flavor was there, but it should have been thigh or legs. The breast made it too dry.  It didn’t seem too busy, but their service wasn’t the best. Moroccan food is eaten with your hands and bread, so we asked for extra bread to eat the Tagine, but it took like 10 minutes to get it. My husband had to get up and ask someone else.  We were going to get the Moroccan tea, but just by looking at it, we knew it was not Moroccan. A mint leaf does not go in the tea cup.
One of the best restaurants in Chicago! The people he are very friendlyand will be very happy to tell you about their country.
Amazing. Delicious. Authentic

Love this place! I tried to order fish on the couscous and was told no. At first I was annoyed, but then our server came back and explained why. It has to do with history of the food in Morocco and the tradition of how food is prepared and put together. Everything always tastes delicious and the service is usually pretty good. It takes a long time for the food to cook once you sit down, but that’s because they aren’t skimping on the tradition of how it’s made.
Unique traditional food very delicious and gracefully served

RUDE and Attitude is terrible. We walked in at 4:45 pm, lights are on and doors are open. The Moroccan owner came running and pushed the door at us yelling:  we are closed look at the sign it says 5 . Then he knocks at the sign hard with his finger.... really? Then you better keep those doors closed then or be nice to perspective customers.
The food is very authentic. The atmosphere is lovely. The owner is very friendly. We keep coming back.
One of my favorite places ever! The lamb is amazing!
Food was delicious!  Excellent service.  Was worth driving over 30 miles.

Not much of a review person but I have to give some good words for Shokran. Food is simple amazing, from the appetizer to main course. Definitely try their lamb it’s delicious. I loved the atmosphere of the restaurant very exotic decoration to the music and the service was cool genuine and friendly. Will definitely go back with my hungry stomach!

This place is sort of a Moroccon cuisine hidden gem in Chicago. You must try their house special Lamb tangines and lamb kebabs.The place was pretty packed on a Friday night but the service was adequate and of course the food was amazing.Everyone at the table was raving about their dishes and my favorites were the Lamb Fez, sweet lamb couscous. I would definitely come back for more.
Food was great and reasonably priced i love it
I was with friends today we had bad service so it gonna be last
Green tea, couscous, lamb and bread was amazing.
Amazing food and service! Our sever was attentive and he taught us a bit about Moroccan culture and how to properly pour tea!
This Restaurant is Just The Best and the Food is the Best of The Best !
The food was delicious! Had the Lamb Fez the lamb was melt in your mouth tender! Will definitely be back!!

Terrible  service from A to Z  , i highly do not reccomend it for moroccans  because food is not moroccan . I asked for authentic moroccan   tea pot  which they advised they do  but it turned to be tea bag  poured info pot  w mint  when i check beneath mint there was no tea . Tea tasted so bad  i returned  it back but still charged me . Couscous  not  complete i still can smell  the dough . Does not accept  cards but  ATM there$  2.75 fee  only cash to evade taxes of course . Not coming back  and i did not leave  any tip of course.
Tagine Chicken was amazing, mint tea was great service was great good place to eat
I was impressed by the quality of food. Authentic Morocco food.
Perfect example of great things come in small sizes. Delicious food, plenty options, good portion, reasonably priced, friendly staff!
Best food ever very delicious and great service Thanks imad
Best Moroccan restaurant ever owner very friendly and food is delicious
Tasty food- lamb is amazing! Not traditional american restaurant where the server is trying to get rid of you and take the next costumer. Its really slow and calm.
Really yummy take-out.................
So delicious!
Good food, nice presentation , good service.  I'll be back.
The coscos was really delicious, the Casablanca lamb was exceptional and the moroccan tea is super good ive never tasted a tea like that
Sumptuous. Some of the best Moroccan I've ever had. I'm looking forward to systematically eating my way through their menu over the next year or so.
great food great service. clean and mix of traditional and Modern ambiance.
Great food and great service. This is my family’s favorite neighborhood restaurant, and we come here at least 2-3 times a month.
This place never disappoints. Wednesday they have any Couscous for $11 (normally $18-20)  cash only but BYOB. Very friendly staff and they take reservations for any size party
Fun place to taste delicious Moroccan dishes
One of my favorite places!
Best ribs ever 💯👍

Experienced best authentic moraccan food in a long time.  My husband ordered his favorite lamb shank tagine which didn't seem to have much meat on the giant bone.  Otherwise taste and variety of food is great.
Absolutely delicious
I loved the food and service at Shokran. We started with the veggie sampler. we then had the Moroccan soup. We shared the vegetarian couscous. The food was cooked to perfection.

This place doesnt look like much on the outside but inside is a different story.  We were seated immediately with our reservation.  They have a BYOB and cash only policy at the time of this visit.  We were given a carafe of water with lemon with our menus a long with some pita bread pieces and sides if black olive slices and a red sauce.  We ordered 3 appetizers to share and 3 entrees.  One was beets & tomatoes, one shrimp in red sauce and finally shredded chicken in Philly.  Entrees were a lamb Casablanca, chicken Casablanca and a salmon with vegetables.  The starters were prepared appropriately and had good taste.  Each of us enjoyed our entrees.  The lamb was especially tender.  Since none of our 3 tangines were got and the lamb was a shank which was larger than the tagine, I believe the food was cooked in something different then placed in the tagine.  For my own taste, the spices were very underutilized and lacked robust flavoring.  We were treated to some desserts and mint tea, which was delicious.  The service is very good, attentive without being troubling.  I would certainly return and eat here again.

Excellent food and service! We were transported to Morocco through the lovely trappings, music and delicious food. Staff are courteous and attentive. They accept cash only which was perfectly fine as we knew this in advance of our visit. The beet & tomato salad was a perfect balance of flavor. And the sweet chicken couscous & tilapia tagine were delightful. Parking can be a challenge but Shokran is just 1/2 block east of the blue line and the experience is well worth the effort.
A "hidden gem" is right. Food was perfectly prepared as usual.  Vegetable Couscous is a great choice and always get the mint tea...
The lamb fez was amazing  omg perfection
Excellent food!

Okay . . . I just wrote a very long review about our recent experience - but some how I lost it. Here is the abridged version. Service seriously is the WORST ever. We arrived at 7:30 and left at 10:00 - not because we wanted to. Took 60 mins to place our entree order. "I'll be back," was the response when we BEGGED our server to place our dinner selection.  Food was pretty good, but I don't know who authentic it is. My wife is Persian, and it's like the same meals we regularly eat - albeit couscous rather than basmati rice.  (It's 4000 mile from Casablanca to Tehran. So, I think "Moroccan" at Shokran may be short for "Middle Eastern.")  BYOB is good. Cash only is good because you can tip the server less; but probably more than they deserve. I have definitely put Shokran on my DNR ("Do Not Return") list.
Ordered one of the tajene  meals. It was delicious, definitely not enough for 2 people! Wonderful atmosphere, felt like I was in Morocco
The quantity and the prices doesn't match.

(Original) An excellent restaurant! great service and warm environment.  Delicious and authentic  Excelente y muy rica comida además del personal sumamente gentil.

WOW WOW WOW !!! when i first saw the place on googlemaps was because i was stying for a few nights in the neighborhood and i wanted to eat something fast . this place was beyond my expectations ! the staff is very nice and welcoming and also can advice about the menu . me and my friend had the hummus and the eggplant for the starter they were delicious (i am israeli and i have tried a few good hummus places in my life ) so this one the best i've tasted in all the USA. for the main course i had the tagin veggies and again wow! , i am vegan so i didn't had any meat or fish but the vegetables were delicious! most of the nonvegan place have very poor vegan meals but not this one. i will deffinite i will definitely visit again when i am in chicagoo!
Cash only place, mediocre quality, cozy place.

The food here is great. Some of the best lamb I've had anywhere. Reasonable corkage fee for BYOB.

Superb, romantic please filled with tapestries, tangines, and great ceremony. Great combinations of savory and sweet, with nuts and plums and other tantric combinations. Elegant plating, personal service. Can't wait to go back.

I love mint tea:) their hummus is so good.... I always eat too much before my main meal. I usually go with group of people so we can order different dishes. Lamb tagin is my favorite yet couscous is pretty good too:)  **Cash Only**

Definitely sit in one of the back rooms. They are prettier and more comfy than the front. Service was outstanding. The staff was so welcoming; the owner even went around to see that every table was happy. Everything we had was delicious.
A great little sit down restaurant with some great authentic Moroccan food! It's certainly not a quick place to eat, but if you aren't tight on time, the wait is definitely worth it!

One star because of the service. The food was good but the staff did not pay any attention to our table. Probably cause we were the only Indian couple there. Had to wait more than 30 minutes for the check till I caved in and walked up to the front desk to settle the bill. Pathetic date experience. Never visiting again !

This has been a favorite of ours for some time. The appetizers, soup, absolutely delicious. The tagines are a must. BE AWARE, CASH ONLY I do wish this wasnt the case, we would have spent more tonight if we didnt have to watch our pennies.
Great authentic food and excellent service!
Make sure to get the Lamb Marrakech!
Great food and service.
Wonderful
If you like lamb, try their couscous. Also do the hummus, it's a must!
Great vegetarian options. Bring cash, no credit cards accepted. Great food, good price.

Good food and good service, I had the Royal couscous and my wife had the Mixed Grill with merguez. Both were delicious. Service was attentive and always checked on us. For dessert, the morrocan mint tea was just the right amount of warm sweetness. :)

(Translated by Google) Honestly a real treat the bast is just beautiful I highly recommend it you would not be disappointed  (Original) Honetement un vrai régal la bouf est juste magnifique je le recommande vivement vous ne serais pas déçu
Simply loved it ..
Great food, great service, and wonderful atmosphere.

OMG, this place is awesome! The dishes are all  prepared with fresh healthy ingredients that bring your palate to Morocco. We had the atlas chicken and lamb shank tanginess (a clay cooking dome that keeps moisture and flavor in each dish).... both were tender,  full of flavor,  and complimented with fresh vegetables.  A great place with great service and reasonable prices!
Really good food excellent  service
Classic Moroccan comfort food. Cozy rooms, small corkage fee for BYOB.
Absolutely amazing!!
Food was great wait staff is super friendly and very attentive. Place is cash only so come prepared.

Great food, good prices,  amazing service! We live in suburbs and I if have to deal with traffic and parking when coming to the city, it better be worth it. Our pleasant experience was something to talk about. Also, we had 2 meat eaters and 2 vegetarians in our group and everyone was happy with meal options.

I have been walking past this restaurant for months now as I make my way to the "El". This Saturday my girlfriend and I decided to pull the trigger and try it out. After a quick glance at the menu and all the positive reviews online I knew we would be alright. The atmosphere was very cozy and casual. It would be a good spot for both a romantic evening with a loved one or hosting a large get together. The food is fantastic and portion sizes are extremely generous (I will be eating some of my GF's Lamb for lunch today) and you definitely get a lot for your money. I think our eyes were bigger than our stomachs. Next time we may just get one entree to share (we both filled up with Pita/Hummus and Bastilla as appetizers). Make sure you have cash as their is no ATM on site (Walgreen's next door has an ATM) and they are "cash only". They are BYOB so we also enjoyed some wine we brought with us. No corking fee. So happy to have a "spot" in my neighborhood. I will definitely continue to bring my friends and family here!
Excellent and authentic Moroccan food.great atmosphere.

Oh. My. Word. This place is amazing, not only authentic, but very friendly and a nice atmosphere as well. The dishes are generously sized and crammed with flavor. I cannot recommend this place enough. The only issue is that they are cash only, which I would take away a half a star if I could.

I really tend not to write negative reviews, but I just had a shockingly terrible experience here. My Lamb Couscous was dry and flavorless all around. The lamb itself was bone dry and almost powdery, and was also cold like it had been sitting out for some time. The waiter asked how everything tasted, and I said mine was a bit dry and bland, and he went on a tirade about how I didn’t understand authentic Moroccan food. This waiter even brought other customers into the conversation. This exchange went on for some time. He then snatched my plate and the plate of my partner who was still eating. There was no apology, but he did take it off the bill, which I appreciated as the single entree was $18. I then heard him stomping around the restaurant like a child throwing a tantrum. It was totally surreal. Also heads up, they’re cash only.
nice place. friendly service. good food
Very good customer service not pushy and very good food we enjoyed our meal very well
The food was wonderful and the service was spectacular. Portions are extremely fair. Just make sure you have cash.

Delicious! We just recently moved to the area, and this was the first restaurant we chose to visit. We were not disappointed. The atmosphere is great, and the servers were so nice and attentive. I got the harira soup and the vegetable tagine and loved it. My partner got the carrot salad and the lamb Casablanca and was equally impressed.
Fantastic service and very authentic Moroccan food!
Great food, accommodating staff. BYOB, cash only, which is a bit of a pain.
Love monday special
The food here was delicious, but the service was poor. My sister, aunt & I did not feel welcomed there.
Delicious Moroccan food  , customer service is good but can be better , coming back again.

My friend is new to the neighborhood and this was a perfect way to celebrate! The food was delicious and our server Aimat took the time to describe the dishes and make recommendations. The lamb fes was outstanding!

Excellent food in a comfortable atmosphere. Service here is not your typical pushy check in every 5 minutes so they can get you out the door faster. They are very attentive in a non disruptive fashion. I have yet to be dissappointed by any dish I have ordered, but be aware the fes dishes are rather sweet, and to the American palate might serve better as a shared side dish.
The food was delicious and the service is spectacular.
Amazing Food great service and good prices.
Very friendly late 1950's atmosphere with excellent Moroccan food.
Was very impressed its a hidden gem service was on point and the food was delicious ,our waiter was very informative about moracco a place we are visiting next month.

One of the best restaurant in Chicago , I have to visit it every time I am there , good Moroccan food, my fav sweet lamb chips , place is nice and of course loved the mint tea Cash only and they have ATM inside the restaurant so no issue ;)

Consistent, high quality, and very tasty Moroccan cuisine. This place is a must. Tagines, Kebobs, and Couscous all outstanding. Sane for appetizers and salads, especially chicken bastilla, which is superb.  Do not miss out on this place. They are LEGIT

Good Moroccan food both in portion and taste! The lamb shank in any combination are all juicy flavorful and fall off the bone tender, the cous cous is buttery and satisfying. The vegetable combo appetizer is very delicious with hot pita pockets. The chicken pie appetizer is too sweet, the beef meatballs are too dry. Service was lacking, the waiter was missing throughout the meal, only to bring us the food and check. But the bus boy was great to refill water consistently. Metered and free street parking available, reservation recommended, cash only.
Delicious food, excellent service!

Shokran remains one of my fave spots to eat delicious, fresh and healthy food. If Moroccan food sounds too exotic to you, and you're concerned about spices or etc.,don't worry! Each of the meal featured in menu truly satisfies taste buds without being too strong...  I always feel welcomed there. Interior resembles key aspects of Moroccan style.  Great place to sit down with family and friends or simply by yourself... Highly recommend!

First time experiencing such a multitude of flavor. Went with friends, and each dish from appetizers,  deserts, main dishes, an hot peppermint tea at the end. Were fantastic and will definitely make a return trip

Love love love this place. We have been there dozen of times, with all of our friends- and everyone loved it. Try lamb - crowd favorite. Fresh food, attention to detail, authentic- must try. Our waiter gave us a small talk about Moroccan cuisine which was very informative. Service was great, by the way.
Words cannot explain how amazing this food was and how authentic the environment was. EXCELLENT
Amazing, the chicken Bastille changed my life.

One of the best meal I had in Chicago. Best Moroccan food I ever ate. The appetiser we ordered was something called Bastille, was yum. In the main course, I ordered a royal Platter of couscous. This was huge in its portion size. But my friends went for lamb tazine, surprisingly that does not some with anything like couscous/ rice/ pita. The chicken kabob was okay, not the best one. Over all it was good for the money. But the problem is that, they take only cash !! It was not an issue for us that day, but it’s a big deal usually ! Also, they charged huge gratuity even we went in a group of three! However, the sitting place inside was good, nicely decorated like a Bedouin camp.

We came from Toronto to spend few days in the city, this was one of the best places we had good authentic food at. Emad, the waiter was such an amazing host. We had the royal couscous, don't forget to enjoy the complementary hot sauce (moroccan hareesa) and the black olives, with toasted pita bread.

Wow! The food was absolutely phenomenal. I ordered a variety of dishes and I was not disappointed in the slightest bit. Everything was very reasonable priced. Aimad was a fantastic server and so incredibly knowledgeable about the food and such a great informative guide on Moroccan traditions, food and culture. I will definitely be returning!
Great fresh food, generous portions, reasonable prices and very knowledgeable and thoughtful service. The best.
Extremely tasty food, in pleasant surroundings plus extremely courteous service.
Delightful atmosphere, great great food, good price.
SO GOOD! Get anything with the merguez. Also this place is byob.

A good friend of mine invited my wife and I out to dinner. He wanted us to try this place since it is one of his favorites and my wife and I never had Moroccan food before. I have to say, they did not disappoint. The service and food was amazing. They also service some of the best teas (Benjamin Tea) that I have ever had! I will definitely re-visit Shoran in the future and recommend it to people!
Great Moroccan food and fantastic customer service.
Fantastic

The food is really delicious ... I enjoyed so much the harira soup and the couscous... Great authentic cuisine and really friendly service!

I love Moroccan food. I had better. Some of the food tasted reheated. I miss Andalus on Clark which was the best Moroccan restaurant in Chicago and it set the bar too high for me to be able to give a second spot 5 stars!

We enjoyed our visit. The first time we ate Moroccan food. We sat down and the owner picked our meal from appetizers thru desert. Wonderful experience we recommend it to all our friends visiting Chicago.

The food is fantastic. It's very affordable, but only cash is accepted. Most authentic Moroccan food I've found in Chicago.

Excellent food. Great decor. Great service. They do not take credit cards though. Dinner for two with appetizer and dessert and tips $50 max is you order the most expensive dishes. No alcohol. One choice of dessert. You would never know how nice it is inside from outside, just do not sit by the LED fireplace (that is the only downer). Try the mint tea.

ALWAYS an amazing meal.  Lamb Fez is killer

Shokran i est inside ite beautiful inside I haven't tried you Arabia full yet it must be good never tried it but it's always a first time

this place is amazing, highly recommend their tagine or couscous. pretty cool atmosphere as well if you sit in the back room
Delicious! Excellent service!  Extensive menu will bring us back many, many times.  Yum!
Fantastic food with a friendly staff. Ordered the salmon tajin, kefta with eggs, bastilla, and mint tea.  All were delicious.  50 per person. With tip.

I have been coming to Shokran since it opened a number of years ago. And I keep coming back because the food is wonderful. Try the Fes/Fez dishes, the tangines, any lamb dish. Actually, every thing I have ever had here is delicious. The people are so nice too. I love coming here. Always.
Very clean good service i will definitely go back again

The food was so good! It's a cozy place, with a good atmosphere. I'll be back to try the other meals on the many that I had my eye on!

authentic experience. so authentic the water they served was probably straight from the native country. terrible. food---subpar. a better dining experience and service may have helped a bad situation better, but unfortunately that wasn't the case.
Good Moroccan food
The food and the staff are amazing. You are treated like family while you are there!

Tradicional Moroccan place, nice decoration and environment. We ordered the chicken bastille as a hot appetizer and it was delicious! I highly recommend it. We also ordered the beef kabab but I wasn't impressed. If you like tea, you should try it here. They are a cash only, but they have an ATM inside. They also charge a $5 if you bring your own bottle but they don't have wine on the menu so I was upset about that. I will try other places before considering going back.
If you like to experience, foreign, and exotic food then you should definitely give this a chance if you love to have new and different experience with food.

Really amazing spiced food. The bread they bring you to start with is good, but made great by the spicy dip, and the seasoned olives on the side.  Chicken bastilla was almost like a desert and the grilled skewers I had were cooked perfectly with juicy meat.  I was also told the food here is all Halal!
Cuscus lamb was super good!! Go try
A cozy and tasty restaurant managed by its friendly and gregarious owner. You can show up with a group and he'll create a delicious menu for you. BYOB.
Great service, great authentic food.
Very good Moroccan food. The lamb tagine is great.
Best Merguez in Town!
Very authentic coudine, decor and place itself.  Extremely nice hosts!  Delicious food and suoetir Moroccan tea! BYOB.  Cash only.   ATM in premises.  Street parking.
Good Moroccan food in a cozy environment

I had an amazing time and ate to my hearts content. The salmon, the lemon chicken and the slow cooked lamb was amazing! Slow cooked food at restaurants is a rare find, but the craftsmanship and patience in making authentic Moroccan food comes through the flavors! Thank you!  Shokran! I look forward to coming back soon!
Excellent authentic Moroccan food. Tastes great, reasonably priced, good portions.
Food is good. Vegetable tagine has MSG in it.

Shokran provided many things well: food, service, ambience, authenticity, and lamb. Did I mention I love lamb? They serve good portion sizes and ample seasoning, leaving you full of Mary's tears as you leave. Cash only is annoying, it is also a bit hard to find, but definitely worth a trip!
Food is delicious! Warm ambiance and great service!
I went once, about a year and a half ago. I still dream about this place. SO GOOD!!!
The food was excellent,  the service outstanding.
I've been to Morocco and this food met those standards. Warm atmosphere and great food. Cash only & BYOB!

I'd only write a review if it was worth sharing. I had a pleasure working with a great Moroccan dishes at Shokran Restaurant. By far one of the best food I've ever been photograph! The food was delicious, the venue was perfect, and everyone was so helpful. Also thank you for taking such great care of us for our anniversary dinner. It was an exceptional experience.
The Kebabs are very good.
delicious authentic Moroccan food

We visited based on the recommendation of the owner of Versailles Cafe, and I'm glad he pointed us here! This is an authentic Moroccan restaurant with a warm ambiance. They don't serve alcohol, but it is a BYOB establishment, so we walked over next door and brought a bottle of wine. We ordered the chicken tagine and chicken bastille, which were both excellent! The owner was very friendly too and we found out the word 'assasin' comes from the Arabic word 'hashasheen.' Very interesting!
Outstanding ethnic food. BYOB, but u can bring whatever u like. The service was not only professional but also very polite ;)
Very good food. The chicken fes tagine was delightful and something new for me. All the food had very good flavors. The mint tea was great too. BYOB.

I love this place. Wonderful authentic Moroccan cuisine in a warm, comfortable setting. The staff is great. The food has to be experienced. After eating here a couple of times, we had them cater a party for about 80 people. It was flawless and everyone loved the food. Go to Shokran! You won't be disappointed.

I felt so sad. I made reservations for 12 and only 5 people came. I had no idea that this would happen. I was scolded by the owner publicly which was so embarrassing. Surely, no one with any intelligence would believe that I planned for people not to come. Then, our meals were never brought. I watched others around me getting their meals and sadly felt I was being punished for the fact that my entire party didn't attend.  Sigh. I will never return. I paid for the food, took it home and didn't even want it. The people who did appear did the same. In business, things happen. I've been in business for 25 years and telling a new customer off because you're frustrated is untenable. I was ashamed for myself and everyone I convinced to spend the evening with me at this place.  I drove 31 miles to waste my time. Never again.

Food is extremely flavorful and authentic (we've been to Marrakesh). Service is attentive.  Gets full on the weekend,  so make a reservation. Also,  we were asked to leave after 2 hours,,  they said the table was reserved for the next party. 😕
Amazing food and amazing staff... My favorite place!
Excellent flavor!!! This was our first time trying Moroccan food and we were not disappointed. We had the kefta and lamb Casablanca which both were amazing. We will definitely be back :-)

This place in my opinion is highly overrated I don't understand what everyone sees in it the protein options aren't that good the flavor is in great the race is decent all these great reviews on Google and Yelp don't make a lot of sense to me
The cous cous is excellent
Ultra disappointing. False representation of Moroccan food

Surprisingly good food! My wife and I went because it's in the area and wanted to try something new. We didn't know what to expect when the did came out. We ordered some of the favorites of he menu and it was really good. Sweet and savory all at the same time.  Would definitely go back again, but make sure to bring cash as its cash only.
The food is Amazing. Especially the Lamb Fez and Lamb Maraksh...totally out of this world. From a true North African source.
Spectacular food, ambience and service!
Amazing!

Having been to Morocco several times i was full of anticipation about trying this restaurant. The ambiance was great and the service was wonderful; the waiter took the time to explain several dishes to my friends and gave a bit of history relating to their origins in Morocco as well. We tried four dishes in all and every one of them was authentic and loaded with fresh vegetables and savory tender meats; the flavors were amazing!  The hummus was the best i have ever had, of course, it too was homemade and fresh!  Shokran is a unique Chicago experience and should be on your "gotta try" list if you love uniquely delicious dishes. Since it is a BYO restaurant we also saved over $56 which more than covered the cost of all our dinners!!!
Love the food and the service is the best
GREAT experience. CLEAN.

Awesome Moroccan food with the BEST service. Our server was from Morocco and was so friendly and helpful. We loved the Chicken Bastilla, couscous, and lamb tagine. And try their Merguez--a house-made sausage.
The food at Shokran is excelente!

One of very few Moroccan restaurants in Chicago.  The decor is a little tired, but it feels like stepping into another world when you walk in.  Choose between typical western table seating, or perching on pillows.  Perfectly blended moroccan mint tea!
The service is slow, but the tajines are really good and worth the wait

We had one of our best meals at Shokran. Every dish was delicious and the service was excellent. We had a four course meal for $35/person which is a great deal for the quality of the food. We're already planning our next trip to Shokran.
This place is awesome and great 1st time experience...staff is wonderful.  Love it
